dc_title_s: The Balkans 1:250,000. Pljevlja, sheet Y-36. A.M.S. M506 (G.S.G.S. 4413)
dc_description_s: Great Britain. War Office. General Staff. Geographical Section. G.S.G.S. 4413. Alternate title: Pljevlja. Lambert conical orthomorphic projection. Danube zone. Gradient tints and isogonic data deleted by AMS, 1949. Relief shown by 50 and 100 meter contour intervals and spot elevations. With Serb and Croat and Albanian glossaries. Intelligence reports up to Jan. 1943. Compiled and drawn by War Office, 1943. See index. Library holdings for this set are incomplete. Geographic location is designated as Yugoslavia it is now Serbia and Montenegro.
dc_publisher_s: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, U.S. Army, 1949.
